¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ \ssection{Definition} ‚¶â
‚¶â

¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ A ‚ù¨list‚ù≠ (or ‚ù¨finite sequence‚ù≠, ‚ù¨string‚ù≠, ‚ù¨$n$-tuple‚ù≠) is a
    family (correspondence) whose index set is $\set{1, ‚Ä¶, n}$
    for $n ‚àà ùó°$. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ The ‚ù¨length‚ù≠ (or ‚ù¨size‚ù≠) of a list is the size of its
    index set, $n$. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ When the codomain of the sequence is a set $A$, we say
    that the sequence is ‚ù¨in‚ù≠ $A$ or that it is a sequence
    ‚ù¨of‚ù≠ elements of $A$. ‚¶â
‚¶â

¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ If $a: \set{1, ‚Ä¶, n} ‚Üí A$ is a sequence, we refer to
    $a(k)$ as the $k$th ‚ù¨term‚ù≠ (or ‚ù¨entry‚ù≠, or
    ‚ù¨element‚ù≠
